cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the theoretical concept of physical-layer network coding and its capacity. 
2) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of a PNC system and its performance in wireless relay networks. 
3) cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper addresses the practical challenges of channel alignment and complexity reduction in PNC systems. 
4) cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions the throughput performance of the PNC system in mobile non-LoS scenarios. 
5) cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of network coding and information transmission.
